memspec does NOT depend on allium-tools as a Cargo crate. We read
allium-tools' parser source code (crates/allium-parser/src/) for
architectural patterns: hand-rolled single-pass lexer with byte-span
tracking, uniform `BlockDecl { kind, name, items }` AST shape, JSON-
emitting diagnostic format, and span-bearing tokens. Implementations
in this repository are written from scratch against memspec's slot
grammar (cells / derived / associations / events / fallible-ops /
state-after-failure / forbidden-states / kill-tests), which is
structurally different from allium's behavioural-DSL grammar.

